            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "What is a Kami?",
                    "type": "sidebar",
                    "text": "The spirit creatures known collectively as kami were originally protectors of the natural world, especially those things unable to protect themselves. Over time, though, their remit has grown, and now kami protectors extend their services to include artificial structures and items. In theory, any animal, plant, object, or location could be served by its own kami, but not everything has yet been blessed with such protection. The classification of which objects warrant kami protection\u2014and those that don\u2019t\u2014is confusing and complicated to all save the kami, who find the organizational system perfectly logical.",
